@paulk-asert Since this pull request seems to be abandoned, I took a look at making the changes you suggested.

It seems like it is not possible to add this feature to the `SimpleStrategy`. When you replace `getInstancePropertyFields(buildee)` with `getSuperPropertyFields(buildee)` the test for the simple strategy still fails with  `The return type of Person setAge(int) in Person is incompatible with void in Mamal`. 

As `SimpleStrategy` does not support most of the other configuration options, I guess this is o.k.? What do you think?

@tkruse That is exactly\* the information I was looking for.  Thank you so much, sir!  (And I hope you're feeling better soon— blech.)

@PascalSchumacher And thank you, sir!  I've been having problems importing the whole Groovy project into Eclipse with BuildShip— I've got it hobbling along enough to navigate the code, but I'm getting things such as

```
A cycle was detected in the build path of project 'groovy'. The cycle consists of projects {groovy, groovy-ant, groovy-groovydoc, groovy-templates, groovy-xml, groovy-test, groovy-bsf, groovy-console, groovy-swing, groovy-docgenerator, groovy-groovysh, groovy-jmx, groovy-json, groovy-jsr223, groovy-macro, groovy-nio, groovy-servlet, groovy-sql, groovy-testng}
```

...but I think my major problems were build fails due to... license checks?  Afraid I don't really understand what's going on with all that.

Anyhow— I'll give it a go and see where we get.
